# TESTING IS MANDATORY

## Test-First Protocol
1. Write a failing test that defines expected behavior
2. Implement minimum code to make it pass
3. Refactor while keeping tests green
4. If ANY pre-existing test fails: STOP and report. DO NOT modify the failing test.

## Coverage Requirements
- Unit tests for exported functions and components
- Integration tests for tRPC procedures (success + error paths)
- E2E tests for user-facing flows
- Minimum 80% coverage on new code
- 100% coverage on auth and data mutation logic

## Test Structure (AAA)
- Arrange — set up test data and mocks
- Act — execute the function/component
- Assert — verify the outcome

## What to Test
- Happy path and error path
- Auth boundaries (unauthenticated, wrong role)
- Database constraints (unique violations, FK violations)
